			<b>
				<span id="how">
					<h3>1) What is Single Sign-On (SSO)</h3>
				</span>
			</b>
			<br />
			<table border="0">
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<b>Current situation</b>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td style="vertical-align: top;">
						<a href="/euu/layout/images/umbrella1.png" rel="lightbox[how]" title="Status Quo">
							<img src="/euu/layout/images/umbrella1.png" width="300px" />
						</a>
					</td>
					<td style="vertical-align: top;">
						<ul>
							<li>The person Peter Fischer has 4 different accounts at photon and neutron research facilities.</li>
							<li>He has to remember 4 different username and password combinations.</li>
							<li>Probably 4 different tools for data access.</li>
						</ul>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<b>Umbrella situation</b>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td style="vertical-align: top;">
						<a href="/euu/layout/images/umbrella2.png" rel="lightbox[how]" title="Status with Umbrella">
							<img src="/euu/layout/images/umbrella2.png" width="300px" />
						</a>
					</td>
					<td style="vertical-align: top;">
						<ul>
							<li>Peter Fischer creates an Umbrella account.</li>
							<li>He connects his Umbrella account with his 4 existing accounts at photon and neutron
								research facilities by login in to the
								application.</li>
							<li>Now he just need to remember his Umbrella username and password to gain access to all
								his existing accounts.</li>
							<li>The existing accounts are now permanently linked with each others.</li>
							<li>The link can be removed if e.g. an account ceases to exist.</li>
